      ],
      "content": "Connect renders editors inside `#document-editor-container` (outer, `flex-1`) and `#document-editor-context` (inner, `relative h-full`). Both carry `data-document-type` attributes; the inner also has `data-editor`. To scope styles to one editor: `#document-editor-context[data-editor=\"my-editor-id\"] { ... }`. The `data-editor` value comes from the `id` field in the editor module config. Targeting container IDs without data-attribute scoping affects ALL editors. Style imports must go in `styles.css` (not `.tsx` files) for production builds, because `tailwindcss/cli` only processes file imports.",
